  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "There are countless memorable lines in English songs that have resonated with listeners over the years. Here are a few iconic ones that often stand out:\n\n1. **\"Imagine\" by John Lennon**:\n   - \"You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one.\"\n\n2. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen**:\n   - \"Is this the real life? Is this just fantasy?\"\n\n3. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen**:\n   - \"Love is not a victory march, it's a cold and it's a broken Hallelujah.\"\n\n4. **\"Hotel California\" by Eagles**:\n   - \"You can check out any time you like, but you can never leave.\"\n\n5. **\"Let It Be\" by The Beatles**:\n   - \"And when the night is cloudy, there is still a light that shines on me.\"\n\n6. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin**:\n   - \"And if you listen very hard, the tune will come to you at last.\"\n\n7. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston**:\n   - \"And I will always love you.\"\n\n8. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana**:\n   - \"With the lights out, it's less dangerous.\"\n\n9. **\"What's Going On\" by Marvin Gaye**:\n   - \"War is not the answer, for only love can conquer hate.\"\n\n10. **\"Firework\" by Katy Perry**:\n    - \"Baby, you're a firework, come on, let your colors burst.\"\n\nThese lines are not only well-written but also evoke strong emotions and have become ingrained in popular culture.",
